WEBVTT

00:02.790 --> 00:05.080
Narrator: The Egyptian plover
and the Nile crocodile

00:05.080 --> 00:09.380
are an example of a symbiotic
relationship at its finest.

00:09.380 --> 00:10.880
[ Hans Gruber snorts ]

00:10.880 --> 00:13.380
So...we're just watching TV
with the pig now.

00:13.380 --> 00:16.000
Is that it?
Is this my life?

00:16.000 --> 00:17.750
Hans Gruber
has a name, Mama.

00:17.750 --> 00:19.120
We don't name food
in this house.

00:19.120 --> 00:20.540
We eat it.
[ Snorting ]

00:20.540 --> 00:23.170
Mama, he doesn't understand
that you're joking.

00:23.170 --> 00:25.290
I'm not.
I promise you, sweetie.

00:25.290 --> 00:27.040
No one is ever going
to eat Hans Gruber.

00:27.040 --> 00:28.290
He's a member
of our family now.

00:28.290 --> 00:29.830
Uh, Greg, honey.

00:29.830 --> 00:31.080
Can you come join me
at the window?

00:31.080 --> 00:32.210
Why?

00:32.210 --> 00:34.620
So we can look out.

00:34.620 --> 00:36.620
Oh, at what?
I want to have
a private conversation.

00:36.620 --> 00:38.040
Why are you so bad
at this?

00:38.040 --> 00:40.120
[ Snorts ]

00:40.120 --> 00:42.750
Okay, you stay.

00:42.750 --> 00:44.960
You know that reoccurring
fantasy I have

00:44.960 --> 00:46.380
where I accidentally
get locked up

00:46.380 --> 00:48.420
in a mental hospital,
and I get to spend three weeks

00:48.420 --> 00:50.250
alone in bed
with no one bugging me?

00:50.250 --> 00:52.250
I'm familiar with your
psych-ward vacation plan, yes.

00:52.250 --> 00:54.330
Well, I'm this close
to doing it.

00:54.330 --> 00:56.460
How is it that we both
said "no" to a puppy,

00:56.460 --> 00:58.750
yet you took it upon yourself
to bring home a pig?

00:58.750 --> 01:00.540
Mama, guess what.

01:00.540 --> 01:03.250
Hans Gruber and I
have a symbiotic relationship.

01:03.250 --> 01:05.540
I give him food,
and he gives me love.

01:05.540 --> 01:06.880
Amazing.

01:06.880 --> 01:08.290
The pig has to go.

01:08.290 --> 01:10.250
But we've gotten used to having
Hans Gruber around.

01:10.250 --> 01:12.540
This has gone on long enough.
Just fold already.

01:12.540 --> 01:14.290
It's only a matter of time
before he does.

01:14.290 --> 01:15.960
What's that supposed
to mean?

01:15.960 --> 01:17.920
Well, you always give in
eventually.

01:17.920 --> 01:20.540
Is that what everyone
in this house thinks of me --

01:20.540 --> 01:22.250
that I always give in?

01:22.250 --> 01:24.540
Well, guess what --
I'm not giving in on this one.

01:24.540 --> 01:25.790
Ever.
Oh, "ever."

01:25.790 --> 01:27.540
So, then, tomorrow?

01:27.540 --> 01:30.250
What the hell?
I can't get that pillow again.

01:30.250 --> 01:32.540
That's a one of a kind
from T.J.Maxx.

01:32.540 --> 01:34.960
[ Sighs ]

01:34.960 --> 01:39.040
This is me --
forced to eat my anger.

01:39.040 --> 01:40.120
[ Hans Gruber snorting ]
[ Gasps ]

01:41.750 --> 01:42.830
[ Gasps ]

01:42.830 --> 01:43.960
Just give him the M&M'S.

01:43.960 --> 01:44.750
Never!

01:50.040 --> 01:52.880
♪♪

01:52.880 --> 01:56.580
[ Cellphone chiming ]

01:56.580 --> 01:58.380
[ Keypad clacking ]

01:58.380 --> 01:59.380
Why are you sending

01:59.380 --> 02:00.420
slutty emojis to someone

02:00.420 --> 02:01.500
who isn't your nice,

02:01.500 --> 02:02.500
sweet boyfriend, Eyo?

02:02.500 --> 02:04.500
[ Cellphone chimes ]

02:04.500 --> 02:06.830
Who is he?
I'm not telling you
anything.

02:06.830 --> 02:08.500
Not a problem.
I'll just FaceTime him.

02:08.500 --> 02:09.920
Mom, give it back!
Mnh-mnh!

02:09.920 --> 02:11.290
Mom, give me back my phone!

02:11.290 --> 02:12.380
You know what? Fine.

02:12.380 --> 02:13.580
His name is John Reese,

02:13.580 --> 02:14.580
and he's a senior.

02:14.580 --> 02:16.540
A senior?

02:16.540 --> 02:18.170
If that's the best thing that
you have to say about him --

02:18.170 --> 02:20.290
[ Snorting ]
Ah, the McRib is back.

02:20.290 --> 02:22.460
[ Gasps ] I'm gonna stay
on you forever

02:22.460 --> 02:24.120
about this, Taylor!
I'm like herpes!

02:24.120 --> 02:26.420
Katie: What the hell comes out
of your mouth sometimes, Katie?

02:26.420 --> 02:28.790
See, Mama?
He's not expensive.

02:28.790 --> 02:30.170
He eats garbage.

02:30.170 --> 02:32.330
It's every mother's dream
to have a farm animal

02:32.330 --> 02:33.580
consuming trash
in her kitchen.

02:33.580 --> 02:35.250
[ Snorting ]

02:37.620 --> 02:38.620
You'll change your mind

02:38.620 --> 02:39.620
once I've trained him.

02:39.620 --> 02:41.250
So, that's it?

02:41.250 --> 02:42.920
That's your plan --
train the hog?

02:42.920 --> 02:44.040
Yes. Hans Gruber

02:44.040 --> 02:45.790
is an unconventional pet,

02:45.790 --> 02:46.920
but Anna-Kat has really bonded

02:46.920 --> 02:48.210
with him, and you know what?

02:48.210 --> 02:49.710
So have I.
Oh.

02:49.710 --> 02:52.330
Yeah, I don't like the,
uh, hillbilly factor, obviously,

02:52.330 --> 02:54.500
but I'm impressed
that you're not folding.

02:54.500 --> 02:56.380
I've never seen
this side of you before.

02:56.380 --> 02:58.000
Thank you, Oliver.

02:58.000 --> 02:59.790
But Mom's not gonna put up
with it much longer.

02:59.790 --> 03:02.210
If you two decide
to get divorced,

03:02.210 --> 03:05.000
I'll go with whoever
doesn't get the minivan.

03:05.000 --> 03:07.880
Katie?
You're thinking about divorce?

03:07.880 --> 03:10.540
Just walk right in, Viv.
Don't worry about social norms.

03:10.540 --> 03:12.120
We are not getting divorced.

03:12.120 --> 03:13.790
Oh, thank God,
because, Katie,

03:13.790 --> 03:15.920
divorce is not as good
as you think it will be.

03:15.920 --> 03:17.960
Even Greg might be better
than no husband.

03:17.960 --> 03:19.330
Thank you, Viv.
You're welcome.

03:19.330 --> 03:20.330
Hey.
These are for you.

03:20.330 --> 03:22.290
[ Gasps ]
You bought me things?

03:22.290 --> 03:24.750
I wish I could buy things.
I have very little money.

03:24.750 --> 03:27.120
It turns out prenups
are legally binding,

03:27.120 --> 03:30.040
even if you dramatically
rip it up during mediation.

03:30.040 --> 03:32.960
Apparently,
they make copies.

03:32.960 --> 03:34.120
You and Alan had a prenup?

03:34.120 --> 03:35.250
We did.

03:35.250 --> 03:37.580
I'm momentarily not as rich
as I look.

03:37.580 --> 03:40.330
I got the house
but not a lot of actual money.

03:40.330 --> 03:41.290
So, I was hoping
you could teach me

03:41.290 --> 03:43.210
how to do laundry
like poor people do.

03:44.830 --> 03:47.170
Viv, I'm not gonna teach you
remedial housekeeping.

03:47.170 --> 03:48.420
Yay!

03:48.420 --> 03:50.040
Oh!

03:50.040 --> 03:52.120
You're doing it for me!
Love it.

03:52.120 --> 03:54.000
Oh, do I need a ticket
or anything?

03:54.000 --> 03:55.460
No.

03:55.460 --> 03:57.330
Okay. Bye!

03:57.330 --> 03:58.750
[ Door closes ]

03:58.750 --> 04:00.830
This is why having money
is important.

04:00.830 --> 04:03.250
Spencer Blitz
doesn't do his own laundry.

04:03.250 --> 04:04.210
D.C.O.B.

04:05.420 --> 04:07.380
"Dry clean only, baby."

04:07.380 --> 04:10.000
Spencer is the type of greedy,
self-centered person

04:10.000 --> 04:12.000
we don't want Oliver
becoming.

04:12.000 --> 04:14.670
I can't believe you're
still letting him
work for that ex-con.

04:15.500 --> 04:17.620
She wants you to fold on this,
too, but don't do it, Dad.

04:17.620 --> 04:18.790
Stay strong.

04:18.790 --> 04:20.500
Hey, puberty boy.

04:20.500 --> 04:21.670
Nobody asked you.

04:21.670 --> 04:23.290
♪♪

04:23.290 --> 04:25.330
[ Snorting ]
Come on. Come on.

04:25.330 --> 04:27.290
Drop it.

04:27.290 --> 04:28.620
[ German accent ]
Hans Gruber, you're a genius!

04:28.620 --> 04:30.080
[ German accent ]
Ja, schwein!
[ Chuckles ]

04:30.080 --> 04:31.920
[ Normal voice ]
Where you off to?

04:31.920 --> 04:33.420
Uh, I'm picking up dinner

04:33.420 --> 04:35.210
for me and Spencer
from Tavern On Main.

04:35.210 --> 04:36.500
I'm really excited.

04:36.500 --> 04:38.170
I've never had a red lobster
from a restaurant

04:38.170 --> 04:39.880
that wasn't named
"Red Lobster."

04:39.880 --> 04:42.000
You seem to be developing
a real friendship with Spencer.

04:42.000 --> 04:44.670
Seems like that?
Good, then it's working.

04:44.670 --> 04:46.790
Soon, he'll think of me
as the son he never had,

04:46.790 --> 04:48.880
and I'll become the sole heir
to a huge fortune

04:48.880 --> 04:51.120
that he does have.

04:51.120 --> 04:52.880
All that smile's missing
is this.

04:54.380 --> 04:55.880
Ooh, I like that.
I'm gonna use it.

04:55.880 --> 04:58.210
♪♪

04:58.210 --> 05:01.080
Mama. Watch this.

05:04.500 --> 05:06.750
Sit.

05:06.750 --> 05:08.710
Now, stay.

05:08.710 --> 05:09.540
[ Snorts ]

05:12.040 --> 05:14.330
Wow!
I'm impressed.

05:14.330 --> 05:15.500
Good work.

05:17.040 --> 05:19.120
Here. Go ahead.

05:19.120 --> 05:20.790
Open them.
Are you sure?

05:20.790 --> 05:22.620
Yeah, Hans Gruber's
got this down.

05:25.420 --> 05:27.290
[ Squeals ]

05:27.290 --> 05:29.170
♪♪

05:29.170 --> 05:30.540
Just drop the M&M'S!

05:30.540 --> 05:32.000
Katie: Never!

05:33.500 --> 05:35.250
Table looks beautiful,
Oli-boy.

05:35.250 --> 05:36.830
Go ahead and light the candles,
will ya?

05:36.830 --> 05:38.290
Ooh, candlelight.

05:38.290 --> 05:40.170
Hi, guys!

05:40.170 --> 05:41.500
What are you doing here?

05:41.500 --> 05:43.250
Oh, I pulled my hamstring

05:43.250 --> 05:45.670
while I was out running,
and I had to stop to stretch.

05:45.670 --> 05:48.420
I looked out the window,
and there she was --

05:48.420 --> 05:51.250
bent clear over,
wearing the tightest pants

05:51.250 --> 05:54.000
I have ever had the pleasure
of seeing a woman wear.

05:54.000 --> 05:55.620
They're called yoga pants.

05:55.620 --> 05:56.830
Yoga pants?

05:56.830 --> 05:57.960
They're very stretchy.

05:57.960 --> 05:59.460
Oh, you're very stretchy.

05:59.460 --> 06:01.960
[ Both laugh ]

06:01.960 --> 06:04.380
Viv, sweetheart, don't you have
some place you need to be?

06:04.380 --> 06:07.080
Oliver, sweetheart,
I'm supposed to be here.

06:07.080 --> 06:08.880
Spencer invited me
to dinner.

06:08.880 --> 06:10.290
That's my seat.

06:10.290 --> 06:11.920
I'll just go get
the Cristal.

06:11.920 --> 06:13.170
[ Gasps ]
Ooh, I love it!

06:13.170 --> 06:14.580
[ Giggles ]

06:16.120 --> 06:18.170
Viv.

06:18.170 --> 06:19.750
Oliver.

06:19.750 --> 06:21.330
I know exactly
what you're doing.

06:21.330 --> 06:22.540
You need a new rich guy,

06:22.540 --> 06:24.000
and you think you're
gonna take mine.

06:24.000 --> 06:26.170
Oh, I don't think it.
I know it.

06:26.170 --> 06:27.210
Oh, yeah?

06:27.210 --> 06:29.080
What makes you
so sure of that?

06:29.080 --> 06:31.290
Because only one of us
has boobs.

06:31.290 --> 06:34.080
♪♪

06:35.710 --> 06:37.880
Say goodbye to Oliver!

06:37.880 --> 06:39.380
Spencer: Bye, Oliver!

06:42.120 --> 06:43.790
I have to be honest,
Katie.

06:43.790 --> 06:45.920
I thought it would be hard
to be physically attracted

06:45.920 --> 06:48.920
to a 78-year-old man,
but Spencer's so wealthy.

06:48.920 --> 06:49.790
I mean,
I'm not a gold digger.

06:49.790 --> 06:51.080
No, you are not!

06:51.080 --> 06:54.080
But this gold is like
right there,

06:54.080 --> 06:56.250
heaped up in a huge pile.

06:56.250 --> 06:57.880
You'd be crazy
not to pick it up.

06:57.880 --> 06:59.250
I know!

06:59.250 --> 07:01.210
Did you do the yoga-pants
stretch I suggested?

07:01.210 --> 07:02.750
[ Gasps ]

07:02.750 --> 07:04.250
That would've done it.

07:04.250 --> 07:05.620
Almost doing it for me.

07:05.620 --> 07:07.330
Right?!
Mm-hmm.

07:07.330 --> 07:08.750
It was you.

07:08.750 --> 07:10.580
What's that now?

07:10.580 --> 07:12.380
You sent Viv
over to Spencer's

07:12.380 --> 07:14.040
so she could squeeze me
out of the picture.

07:14.040 --> 07:16.710
I was his only friend in the
world until this came along.

07:16.710 --> 07:18.710
Hi.
It's not gonna work.

07:18.710 --> 07:20.620
Spencer and I have something
special together,

07:20.620 --> 07:22.790
and I'm not gonna let you two
get between us.

07:22.790 --> 07:30.620
♪♪

07:30.620 --> 07:33.330
Oliver.

07:33.330 --> 07:34.830
Viv.

07:34.830 --> 07:36.290
That car is gonna shine.

07:36.290 --> 07:37.960
This kid knows how
to take care of me.

07:40.000 --> 07:42.170
Keep walking, blondie.

07:48.500 --> 07:50.250
♪♪

07:50.250 --> 07:51.290
♪ Whoa! ♪

07:51.290 --> 07:52.420
♪ Swingin' in there ♪

07:52.420 --> 07:53.670
♪ 'Cause she wanted
me to feed her ♪

07:53.670 --> 07:55.250
♪ So, I mixed up the batter ♪

07:55.250 --> 07:56.620
♪ And she licked the beater ♪

07:56.620 --> 07:59.460
♪ I scream, you scream,
we all scream for her ♪

07:59.460 --> 08:02.210
♪ Don't even try
'cause you can't ignore her ♪

08:02.210 --> 08:04.830
♪ She's my cherry pie ♪

08:04.830 --> 08:05.830
♪ Cool drink of water ♪

08:05.830 --> 08:07.250
♪ Such a sweet surprise ♪

08:07.250 --> 08:08.500
♪ Tastes so good ♪

08:08.500 --> 08:09.880
♪ Make a grown man cry ♪

08:09.880 --> 08:11.920
♪ Sweet cherry pie ♪

08:11.920 --> 08:12.960
♪ Oh, yeah ♪

08:12.960 --> 08:15.210
♪ She's my cherry pie ♪

08:15.210 --> 08:17.670
I'm soaking.

08:17.670 --> 08:20.250
Would you be a sweetheart
and go get me a towel?

08:20.250 --> 08:22.040
Anything for you.

08:22.040 --> 08:23.210
We're done here, Oliver.

08:25.960 --> 08:33.120
♪♪

08:38.880 --> 08:41.670
Does anyone know what's inside
this container of cream cheese?

08:41.670 --> 08:44.330
Someone wrote "This is not
cream cheese" on it.

08:44.330 --> 08:47.000
Mom, you've dated two guys at
the same time before, right?

08:47.000 --> 08:49.000
Yeah, of course.
Wait.

08:49.000 --> 08:50.960
No.

08:52.210 --> 08:55.040
Ugh.
This is not cream cheese.

08:55.040 --> 08:56.880
Hold that thought.
What are you doing?

08:56.880 --> 08:59.580
Fighting for my man.

08:59.580 --> 09:01.750
I'm gonna introduce Spencer
to the 21st century

09:01.750 --> 09:03.710
using the very Xbox
Viv gave me.

09:03.710 --> 09:05.170
Stay out of Viv's way.

09:05.170 --> 09:06.420
She needs Spencer
more than you do.

09:06.420 --> 09:07.620
How do you figure?

09:07.620 --> 09:09.620
A woman like Viv,
when she sees an opportunity

09:09.620 --> 09:12.040
to better her situation,
she has to grab it.

09:12.040 --> 09:13.670
She's only after his money,

09:13.670 --> 09:15.830
which is gonna be my money --
mine.

09:15.830 --> 09:17.580
Oliver,
for the last time --

09:17.580 --> 09:18.960
[ Snorting ]

09:18.960 --> 09:20.290
There aren't even M&M'S!

09:20.290 --> 09:22.000
Hans Gruber!
It's not easy for me

09:22.000 --> 09:23.170
to jump up on this counter,
Greg!

09:23.170 --> 09:24.330
You know I have a thing
against jumping!

09:26.170 --> 09:28.420
I realize the dog-training-book
approach isn't working,

09:28.420 --> 09:30.250
but I've tracked down someone
who can help.

09:30.250 --> 09:31.460
Do you remember
The Critter Man?

09:31.460 --> 09:33.580
You mean that weird guy
who got those baby raccoons

09:33.580 --> 09:34.620
out of the basement?

09:34.620 --> 09:36.380
And drove them
all the way to Maine

09:36.380 --> 09:38.380
and set them free
by that beautiful lake?

09:38.380 --> 09:41.330
Uh...yeah.
That's what that guy did.

09:41.330 --> 09:43.580
The Critter Man
is gonna drive Hans Gruber

09:43.580 --> 09:45.790
to Maine to live with
the baby raccoons by the lake?

09:45.790 --> 09:47.880
No. He hooked me up
with a pig whisperer.

09:47.880 --> 09:49.080
If you're serious,
I'm gonna drive you

09:49.080 --> 09:50.960
up to Maine
to live by the lake.

09:50.960 --> 09:52.540
We're not getting
a pig whisperer!

09:52.540 --> 09:54.710
First of all, I don't even need
a "first of all."

09:54.710 --> 09:55.830
We're not doing it.

09:55.830 --> 09:57.790
I'm doubling down
on training Hans Gruber.

09:57.790 --> 10:00.250
Everyone expects me to fold.
This is me not folding!

10:02.750 --> 10:04.960
And you need to get used to me
and Spencer being together.

10:04.960 --> 10:06.790
You will not
break us apart.

10:06.790 --> 10:08.330
And I know how that sounds.

10:08.330 --> 10:11.790
♪♪

10:11.790 --> 10:13.330
Now head into
the jungle village

10:13.330 --> 10:15.670
and don't shoot anyone
who isn't holding a gun.

10:15.670 --> 10:19.170
This new technology's
unbelievable.

10:19.170 --> 10:22.000
That little girl hiding behind
the well looks so realistic.

10:22.000 --> 10:23.290
She's got a machete.

10:23.290 --> 10:24.580
She looks so sweet.

10:24.580 --> 10:26.170
I'll just shoot her
in the arm.

10:26.170 --> 10:27.670
Ooh, right in the forehead.

10:27.670 --> 10:29.210
Hey, Spence.

10:29.210 --> 10:30.540
You want to go play tennis
with me out back?

10:30.540 --> 10:32.540
I never want to do
anything else except

10:32.540 --> 10:34.880
play these new,
high-tech video games.

10:36.960 --> 10:38.500
Did you hear that, Viv?

10:38.500 --> 10:40.580
Who has the boobs now?

10:40.580 --> 10:43.580
♪♪

10:43.580 --> 10:45.080
Hey, Spence.

10:45.080 --> 10:46.670
Do you want to go
take a bath?

10:48.380 --> 10:49.880
Get out, Oliver.

10:49.880 --> 10:52.670
♪♪

10:52.670 --> 10:55.290
Okay, first, you need to learn
how to assert dominance.

10:55.290 --> 10:56.880
Let him know
who's in charge.

10:56.880 --> 10:58.670
Never be the one
to break eye contact.

10:58.670 --> 10:59.920
Like this?

10:59.920 --> 11:01.620
Exactly like this.

11:01.620 --> 11:02.960
Do not look away.

11:02.960 --> 11:04.880
Do not show weakness.

11:04.880 --> 11:06.920
You are in charge.

11:06.920 --> 11:10.000
[ Dramatic music plays ]

11:14.290 --> 11:16.120
Are you guys
about to kiss?

11:16.120 --> 11:18.420
I don't know.

11:18.420 --> 11:20.580
Katie:
I've solved my Oliver problem

11:20.580 --> 11:21.960
by getting him away
from Spencer

11:21.960 --> 11:24.250
and Viv's problem by getting her
involved with Spencer.

11:24.250 --> 11:26.040
I've only got
one problem left,

11:26.040 --> 11:28.120
and that problem tastes
really good

11:28.120 --> 11:31.580
with barbecue sauce
and potato salad.

11:31.580 --> 11:32.920
Can't eat the pig,
Katie.

11:32.920 --> 11:34.500
We can't keep it, either.

11:34.500 --> 11:35.710
It's getting bigger
every day.

11:35.710 --> 11:37.380
Seriously, Greg,
just fold already.

11:37.380 --> 11:40.380
[ Dramatic music plays ]

11:40.380 --> 11:42.290
What are you doing?

11:42.290 --> 11:44.000
Nothing.

11:46.290 --> 11:47.580
Kind of feels like
you're doing something.

11:47.580 --> 11:49.080
Nope.

11:51.420 --> 11:53.380
Are you trying
to pig-train me, Greg?

11:53.380 --> 11:54.540
Is that what this is?

11:54.540 --> 11:56.500
Shh.

11:56.500 --> 12:01.960
♪♪

12:01.960 --> 12:03.830
Whatever this is,

12:03.830 --> 12:05.420
you shouldn't be doing it
with the door open.

12:05.420 --> 12:06.670
What do you want,
Taylor?

12:06.670 --> 12:08.120
Can I go to a party?
With who?

12:08.120 --> 12:09.710
John Reese.
Who's that?

12:09.710 --> 12:12.290
He's a senior.
You're dating Eyo!

12:12.290 --> 12:13.670
Yeah, I know,
but I took Mom's advice.

12:13.670 --> 12:15.380
What are you
talking about?

12:15.380 --> 12:18.330
You told Viv to go for a senior.
I'm going for a senior, too.

12:18.330 --> 12:20.540
Better parties,
better social status.

12:20.540 --> 12:22.210
I'm grabbing
a better opportunity.

12:24.120 --> 12:26.420
What did you say to her?
I like Eyo.

12:26.420 --> 12:27.540
He's a good kid,
and we don't know

12:27.540 --> 12:29.170
the first thing
about this senior.

12:29.170 --> 12:31.000
You brought home
a live pig!

12:31.000 --> 12:32.040
You can't keep playing
the pig card.

12:32.040 --> 12:33.830
Oh, I can.
And do you want to know why?

12:33.830 --> 12:35.460
Because it's a pig card!

12:35.460 --> 12:37.580
Ah!
You're driving me crazy.

12:37.580 --> 12:39.330
I must say, this is
a refreshing change of pace.

12:39.330 --> 12:40.330
What does that mean?

12:40.330 --> 12:41.540
Just that usually
you're the one

12:41.540 --> 12:42.710
who does exactly
what she wants,

12:42.710 --> 12:43.880
and I'm forced
to deal with it.

12:43.880 --> 12:45.710
Is that so?
Yeah, it is so.

12:45.710 --> 12:46.960
It is so, so.

12:46.960 --> 12:48.880
It is so, so, so!

12:48.880 --> 12:50.330
We're doing
a pillow wall tonight.

12:50.330 --> 12:52.250
No. My anger's too big
for a pillow wall.

12:52.250 --> 12:53.920
We're going toes to nose.

12:59.250 --> 13:01.420
Greg, why do your feet
look so good?

13:01.420 --> 13:03.380
Are you wasting our money
on pedicures again?

13:03.380 --> 13:05.120
Katie, do you want to have
the pedicure fight

13:05.120 --> 13:06.250
or stick
with this pig fight?

13:06.250 --> 13:07.960
'Cause I'm not folding
on anything,

13:07.960 --> 13:10.580
and it's not a waste of
money if it makes me feel
better about myself.

13:10.580 --> 13:11.620
[ Scoffs ]

13:11.620 --> 13:12.710
♪♪

13:16.830 --> 13:17.920
I feel kind of bad.

13:17.920 --> 13:19.040
I helped Viv get out
of a loveless marriage,

13:19.040 --> 13:20.290
but then encouraged her
to go for Spencer

13:20.290 --> 13:22.380
for no reason
other than money.

13:22.380 --> 13:23.620
If you break up
Viv and Spencer,

13:23.620 --> 13:25.750
Oliver will run
right back to Spencer.

13:25.750 --> 13:28.540
But if you don't do anything,
then you're teaching Taylor

13:28.540 --> 13:30.420
that love is just about
status and money.

13:30.420 --> 13:32.790
Ooh, you have to pick
one child to save.

13:32.790 --> 13:34.290
This is a real
Katie's Choice.

13:34.290 --> 13:36.880
So...which kid
are you gonna save?

13:39.330 --> 13:41.880
I choose to save Taylor.
Mm-hmm.

13:41.880 --> 13:45.250
Because if I let Oliver go down
the Spencer path when he's rich,

13:45.250 --> 13:48.500
he'll put us in one of those
nice, retirement communities.

13:48.500 --> 13:50.790
Not like that rat trap
we'll have to put my mom in.

13:51.620 --> 13:54.170
You guys have to help me
break up Viv and Spencer.

13:54.170 --> 13:56.250
Ooh.
Let's take Viv out tonight.

13:56.250 --> 13:58.920
We can help her find someone
else so she forgets him.

13:58.920 --> 14:00.000
Are you guys in a rush?

14:00.000 --> 14:01.420
No.
Not really.

14:01.420 --> 14:02.920
Good, because I need
at least 20 minutes

14:02.920 --> 14:05.380
to complain about Greg
and his stupid pig.

14:05.380 --> 14:08.790
It makes so much noise,
and it eats the garb--

14:08.790 --> 14:10.920
This is a time where you can
just zone out and let me talk.

14:10.920 --> 14:12.540
Cool.
Cool.

14:12.540 --> 14:14.790
Its snout is just the grossest
thing in the world.

14:14.790 --> 14:16.380
It's wet...

14:16.380 --> 14:19.170
♪♪

14:19.170 --> 14:21.460
Viv, we are taking you
out tonight, okay?

14:21.460 --> 14:23.880
We are going to meet some nice,
eligible men.

14:23.880 --> 14:25.500
Or maybe a woman.

14:25.500 --> 14:26.920
Ooh, I tried that in college
eight times.

14:26.920 --> 14:28.170
It just wasn't for me.

14:28.170 --> 14:30.170
It took you eight times
to figure that out?

14:30.170 --> 14:32.830
Okay.
You guys, I'm fine!

14:32.830 --> 14:34.710
Spencer checks
all the boxes.

14:34.710 --> 14:37.420
He's rich.
There's really just one box.

14:37.420 --> 14:38.880
You need to find
a good guy.
Yeah.

14:38.880 --> 14:40.790
Someone nice who you can
fall in love with.

14:40.790 --> 14:42.330
Like Greg.
Well, thanks, Doris.

14:42.330 --> 14:44.170
But not Greg.
Not ever Greg.

14:44.170 --> 14:46.040
If Katie dies,
I call dibs.

14:46.040 --> 14:48.500
[ Snorting ]
Not my bra, you stupid pig!
Drop it!

14:48.500 --> 14:51.170
Katie, relax.
You're not supposed to yell.

14:51.170 --> 14:52.250
[ Snorts ]

14:52.250 --> 14:54.000
Use a low, calm voice.

14:54.000 --> 14:56.380
In case you haven't noticed,
I don't have one of those.

14:56.380 --> 14:58.210
The pig has got to go!

14:58.210 --> 14:59.620
No!
Yes!

14:59.620 --> 15:02.330
Ladies, I'm sorry you had to see
this side of my marriage.

15:02.330 --> 15:03.790
[ Snorts ]

15:03.790 --> 15:05.380
Excuse me while I storm off
with my pig.

15:05.380 --> 15:07.790
[ Squealing ]

15:10.540 --> 15:12.460
I think I'm just gonna
stick with Spencer.

15:12.460 --> 15:15.000
Ah. Doris, maybe you and I
should go get some wine.

15:15.000 --> 15:16.920
And not come back.
Yeah.

15:20.080 --> 15:21.920
[ Door opens, closes ]

15:21.920 --> 15:23.750
Are you and Daddy okay?

15:23.750 --> 15:26.420
Honey, if two unplanned
pregnancies,

15:26.420 --> 15:28.080
a houseful of lice,
and a move to Westport

15:28.080 --> 15:30.210
can't break us up,
nothing will.

15:30.210 --> 15:32.250
[ Cellphone chiming ]
[ Chuckles ]

15:34.460 --> 15:37.460
John Reese. Okay, I need
to talk to my girls.

15:37.460 --> 15:38.620
That includes you, too,
Viv.

15:43.460 --> 15:45.920
In a relationship --
like in that nature show --

15:45.920 --> 15:49.000
sometimes it's symbiotic
and everything's perfect.

15:49.000 --> 15:51.210
And sometimes it's parasitic

15:51.210 --> 15:53.080
and you want
to throttle each other.

15:53.080 --> 15:54.710
But the important part is

15:54.710 --> 15:58.040
the core of the relationship
never changes.

15:58.040 --> 16:00.000
I have been working
on my core like crazy.

16:00.000 --> 16:03.040
Different core, Viv.
Pay attention.

16:03.040 --> 16:06.330
When I met your daddy,
I knew he was the one for me.

16:06.330 --> 16:09.380
I had dated
a lot of bad boys,

16:09.380 --> 16:12.620
but he was so kind
and so smart...

16:12.620 --> 16:15.330
that I couldn't help
but fall in love with him.

16:15.330 --> 16:17.250
Half the time I didn't know
what he was talking about,

16:17.250 --> 16:20.880
but I got this special feeling
in my stomach,

16:20.880 --> 16:24.500
and that part
never goes away

16:24.500 --> 16:26.500
no matter how many pigs
he brings home.

16:28.330 --> 16:30.080
[ Knock on door ]

16:31.790 --> 16:33.580
Oh, thanks for coming
on such short notice.

16:33.580 --> 16:35.170
Oh, not a problem.

16:35.170 --> 16:37.580
I was just in Wilton
dealing with a depressed
pig, and I was like,

16:37.580 --> 16:39.880
[ Whispering ] "You're just
gonna be such a good pig.

16:39.880 --> 16:41.250
No one's ever
gonna eat that pig."

16:41.250 --> 16:42.460
[ Normal voice ]
And that did the trick.
Mm.

16:42.460 --> 16:45.120
Greg, why is
the Pig Whisperer here?

16:45.120 --> 16:47.210
'Cause I'm not giving up
on Hans Gruber.

16:47.210 --> 16:49.580
Uh...Greg, can you join me
in your office?

16:49.580 --> 16:50.880
Why?

16:50.880 --> 16:53.040
To look over some papers.
What papers?

16:53.040 --> 16:54.000
I want to yell at you
in private.

16:54.000 --> 16:55.500
You're the worst at this!

16:58.710 --> 17:00.580
[ Snorting ]

17:00.580 --> 17:02.250
If this pig
is just about you

17:02.250 --> 17:04.080
proving to everyone
that you don't fold,

17:04.080 --> 17:05.620
then it's time
to pick something else.

17:05.620 --> 17:07.250
Something like you say
you want Mexican,

17:07.250 --> 17:09.040
and I say,
"No, I want Italian,"

17:09.040 --> 17:11.290
and then you say,
"I want Mexican," and
then we have Mexican.

17:11.290 --> 17:13.580
It's not that simple.
[ Sighs ]

17:15.210 --> 17:17.290
When I was five years old,
we had a dog that I loved

17:17.290 --> 17:19.380
more than anything
in the world,

17:19.380 --> 17:21.000
and my very first day
of kindergarten,

17:21.000 --> 17:22.290
I kissed him goodbye

17:22.290 --> 17:24.380
and when I got back home,
he was gone.

17:24.380 --> 17:27.120
My dad had given him away.
I was crushed.

17:27.120 --> 17:29.880
And I can't do that
to Anna-Kat.

17:29.880 --> 17:31.380
I'm sorry.
I just can't.

17:35.120 --> 17:37.210
I've never heard
this story before.

17:37.210 --> 17:39.710
Well, it's not something
I like to talk about.

17:39.710 --> 17:43.290
Just out of curiosity,
what was the dog's name?

17:43.290 --> 17:44.670
Winston.
Winston.

17:44.670 --> 17:45.880
Yeah, 'cause he looked like
Winston Churchill.

17:45.880 --> 17:47.420
Mm-hmm.

17:47.420 --> 17:49.000
I see.

17:49.000 --> 17:50.080
Go ahead and call my mom
and ask.

17:50.080 --> 17:51.420
I'm not calling your mom.

17:51.420 --> 17:53.080
Okay.

17:53.080 --> 17:54.250
I guess the pig
can stay...

17:54.250 --> 17:55.750
[ Snorts ]

17:55.750 --> 17:58.210
...because of this important
story in your life...

17:58.210 --> 17:59.920
that I just heard...

17:59.920 --> 18:02.750
for the first time ever
just now.

18:02.750 --> 18:05.000
Right.

18:05.000 --> 18:07.420
Mm.

18:07.420 --> 18:10.620
♪♪

18:10.620 --> 18:14.580
[ Snorting ]

18:14.580 --> 18:16.000
I know! I know! I know!

18:16.000 --> 18:18.960
You are so funny.

18:18.960 --> 18:21.210
You're so cute
and handsome,

18:21.210 --> 18:23.580
and you don't have that weird,
old-man smell.

18:26.460 --> 18:28.080
I'll be right back.

18:30.460 --> 18:33.670
[ Gasps ] Oh, my God.

18:33.670 --> 18:36.040
I think I know what you
were talking about.

18:36.040 --> 18:39.580
I have that special feeling,
and he asked me out.

18:39.580 --> 18:42.000
You know he's our pig trainer,
and he's 27.

18:42.000 --> 18:44.420
We're the same age!

18:46.790 --> 18:49.500
[ Gunfire ]

18:49.500 --> 18:50.880
I got bad news for you.

18:50.880 --> 18:52.790
Oh, yeah?

18:52.790 --> 18:54.620
Viv met another guy.

18:54.620 --> 18:57.580
Eh, she wasn't the first,
and she won't be the last.

18:57.580 --> 18:59.790
She might be pretty close
to the last.

18:59.790 --> 19:01.750
Next time,
you have to be careful.

19:01.750 --> 19:03.580
There's a lot of people
out there

19:03.580 --> 19:05.670
who just want to be with you
for your money.

19:05.670 --> 19:07.750
Thank you, kid.

19:07.750 --> 19:10.420
So, uh, what do you want me
to pick up for dinner tonight?

19:10.420 --> 19:12.620
Mm...lobster.

19:12.620 --> 19:13.710
For two.

19:15.710 --> 19:17.380
I'll just get my wallet.

19:17.380 --> 19:20.500
[ Bomb whistles, explodes ]

19:20.500 --> 19:27.790
♪♪

19:27.790 --> 19:30.540
What's going on?
Oh.

19:30.540 --> 19:32.460
Taylor was just telling me she's
gonna stop texting John Reese.

19:32.460 --> 19:33.830
Yeah,
it's not fair to Eyo.

19:33.830 --> 19:34.960
Good for you, honey.

19:34.960 --> 19:36.120
Yeah, well done.

19:36.120 --> 19:37.210
Maybe I should text John

19:37.210 --> 19:39.750
and give him some closure.

19:39.750 --> 19:41.210
Nah,
I'm just gonna go dark.

19:43.750 --> 19:46.120
By the way, just got off
the phone with your mom.

19:46.120 --> 19:47.830
You picked up
when my mom called?

19:47.830 --> 19:48.920
Were you buried
under rubble?

19:48.920 --> 19:50.880
I called her to confirm

19:50.880 --> 19:53.000
your dog sob story,
which she did.

19:53.000 --> 19:54.500
Katie.
Don't be mad.

19:54.500 --> 19:56.120
I feel like
I was already punished.

19:56.120 --> 19:59.290
She droned on for 45 minutes
about her latest food allergy.

19:59.290 --> 20:00.580
Lots of bowel talk.

20:00.580 --> 20:02.460
Ah. Dairy.

20:02.460 --> 20:05.880
I'm sorry for doubting
your story about Winston.

20:05.880 --> 20:09.170
And we can keep Hans Gruber
for as long as you want.

20:09.170 --> 20:11.580
Thanks, sweetie.

20:11.580 --> 20:13.250
Well...

20:13.250 --> 20:15.120
I'm gonna go feed our pig
some garbage.

20:18.080 --> 20:20.540
[ Cellphone beeps ]

20:20.540 --> 20:23.250
Mom, thanks for covering for me.
She totally bought it!

20:23.250 --> 20:25.290
I know! I know!
For once, I didn't fold.

20:29.880 --> 20:32.380
You want the last M&M?
I know you like the greens.

20:32.380 --> 20:34.250
[ Snorts ]

20:34.250 --> 20:36.710
Greg, we're all out of M&M'S.
Can you go get us some more?

20:36.710 --> 20:37.830
You're the ones
that ate them.

20:37.830 --> 20:41.250
[ Dramatic music plays ]

20:41.250 --> 20:43.460
The pig stare
is not going to work, Katie.

20:43.460 --> 20:44.460
Don't even try.

20:44.460 --> 20:46.960
♪♪

20:46.960 --> 20:49.790
I'm not moving.

20:49.790 --> 20:53.170
[ Music intensifies ]

20:53.170 --> 20:58.420
♪♪

20:58.420 --> 20:59.420
Okay,
but for the record,

20:59.420 --> 21:00.920
I'm doing this
because I want to.

21:04.380 --> 21:05.960
Who's my good,
little Greg Whisperer?

21:05.960 --> 21:08.080
[ Snorts ]
You are.
